Description:
Brazilian football player Pelé (Edison Arantes do Nascimento) weeps for joy when Brazil wins the FIFA World Cup final after defeating guest land Sweden in Råsunda Stadium in Solna. It was the first time Brazil won the World Cup. 

Pelé is resting his head on the shoulder of his teammate Didi (Waldyr Pereira), on the right, Brazil's goalkeeper Gylmar dos Santos Neves.

Title: Not Specified
Description:
Street fight during the final days of the revolution in Havana, Cuba. 

The Cuban Revolution, which had started in July 1953 with an armed attack on an army base by Fidel Castro and his revolutionary 26th of July Movement, culminated on 1 January 1959 when President Fulgencio Battista fled the country and his army capitulated. The rebellion army led by Che Guevara and Camilo Cienfuegos entered Havana on 2 January, joined by Castro on 8 January.
